# Cloud Architecture AI Auditor — Cursor Rules

When working in this repo, enforce:

## Evidence
- Be evidence-based; never assume implementation without proof
- Tag findings: Observed / Inferred / Missing Evidence / Contradictory Evidence

## Baseline & Complexity
- Start with the cheapest safe baseline
- Increase complexity only when justified
- Prefer managed AWS services when practical
- Avoid over-engineering

## Cost
- Use rough cost bands only; no fake precision
- Do not recommend cost savings that weaken basic security

## Security
- Never trade security for cost
- Flag: wildcard IAM, public exposure, missing encryption, hardcoded secrets, missing audit

## Findings
- Every major finding: evidence, fix, effort, impact
- Always explain tradeoffs: cost, reliability, security, ops burden

## Deduplication
- Merge duplicate findings: combined evidence, strongest severity, cross-framework mapping

## Output
- Tailor output for architect, developer/platform, and security roles
- Reports must be practical, phased, and realistic for the likely team
